The usage of the title '''Golden Book''' includes:
* Golden Books was the children's book imprint of [[Western Publishing]], later Golden Books Publishing and now [[Random House]]/[[Penguin Random House]] * [[Little Golden Books]] and [[Giant Golden Books]] children's series * [[Golden Book Encyclopedia]] * ''[[The Golden Book Magazine]]'', a magazine publishing short fiction that ran from 1925 to 1939 * [[Codex Aureus (disambiguation)|Codex Aureus]] ([[Latin language|Latin]] for ''Golden Book'') are several [[Gospel]] books from the 9th through 11th centuries that were heavily illuminated with gold leaf * [[Libro d'Oro]] ({{lang-en|Golden Book}}) is the official register of the [[Kingdom of Italy]], compiled by consulting heraldry * ''The Golden Book of Marcus Aurelius'', by [[Meric Casaubon]], a translation of ''[[Meditations]]'' by [[Marcus Aurelius]] * ''The Golden Book of Marcus Aurelius'' (1534), by [[John Bourchier, 2nd Baron Berners]] * The ''[[Golden Book of Cycling]]'' was created in 1932 to celebrate "the Sport and Pastime of Cycling by recording outstanding rides, deeds and accomplishments"
