{{Infobox television | show_name = Good Game | image = Good Game Release poster GG YT.jpg | genre = [[Television comedy|Comedy]] | director = Danny Jelinek | writer = {{Plainlist| * Sarah Carbiener * Erica Rosbe }} | creator = {{Plainlist| * [[Jesse Cox (entertainer)|Jesse Cox]] * [[Michele Morrow]] }} | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Dan Avidan]] * [[Arin Hanson]] * [[Michele Morrow]] * Jade Payton * Rahul Abburi * [[Michael Ornstein]] }} | composer = Ryan Elder | country = United States | language = English | num_seasons = 1 | num_episodes = 6 | list_episodes = #Episodes | executive_producer = {{Plainlist| * Arin Hanson * Brent Lilley * Steve Levy * Jen Roskind * Michael Waldron * Sarah Carbiener * Erica Rosbe * Jesse Cox * Michele Morrow * [[Dan Harmon]] }} | producer = | editor = {{Plainlist| *Andy Maxwell *Chris Poole }} | location = | cinematography = Andrew Knapp | camera = | runtime = 25 minutes | company = Starburns Industries | network = [[YouTube Red]] | picture_format = [[4K resolution|4K]] [[Ultra-high-definition television|(UHDTV)]] | audio_format = | first_run = | first_aired = {{Start date|2017|8|30}} | last_aired = {{End date|2017|9|27}} | website = | website_title = }}
'''''Good Game''''' is an American [[Television comedy|comedy]] [[web television]] series, developed by [[Michele Morrow]] and [[Jesse Cox (entertainer)|Jesse Cox]], that premiered on August 30, 2017 on [[YouTube Red]]. In March 2018, it was announced that the show had been cancelled after one season due to low viewership.
==Premise== ''Good Game'' follows "a newly formed team of eSports players trying to make it to the top in the cutthroat world of competitive gaming."<ref name="SeriesOrder">{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=YouTube Red Orders Series Produced By Dwayne Johnson, Dan Harmon & More |url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/youtube-red-orders-series-produced-dwayne-johnson-dan-harmon-1202118716/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |date=June 22, 2017}}</ref>
==Cast and characters== * [[Dan Avidan]] as Alex Taylor, the optimistic coach of the team and Ryland's roommate * [[Arin Hanson]] as Ryland Smith, a former ''[[Defense of the Ancients|DotA]]'' legend who tries to hide his embarrassing past * [[Michele Morrow]] as Ashley "Ash" Donovan, a video game reporter who relishes the chance to compete * Jade Payton as Samantha "Sam" Kinsey, a former Olympic tennis hopeful who began playing ''Killcore'' during rehabilitation from an injury * Rahul Abburi as Kamal Pasala, an obnoxious but vital part of the team. * [[Michael Ornstein]] as Lorenzo Santella Jr., Alex and Ryland's landlord and source of the team's funding * [[Oliver Cooper]] as "SteaminSemen", Ryland's adversary * [[Jesse Cox (entertainer)|Jesse Cox]] as Jesse Newman, the mysterious creator of ''Killcore''
==Production== ===Development=== On June 22, 2017, it was announced during [[YouTube Red]]'s presentation at [[VidCon]] that they had given the production a series order. The series was developed by [[Michele Morrow]] and [[Jesse Cox (entertainer)|Jesse Cox]], executive produced by [[Dan Harmon]], and expected to be showrun by Sarah Carbiener and Erica Rosbe. Production companies involved with the series were expected to consist of Starburns Industries.<ref name="SeriesOrder"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Alexander |first1=Julia |title=YouTube, Dan Harmon are hopping on TV’s newest trend with scripted esports comedy |url=https://www.polygon.com/tv/2017/6/23/15861400/youtube-red-dan-harmon-esports |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |date=June 23, 2017}}</ref>
On March 25, 2018, Morrow announced through her official Twitter account that the show had been cancelled after one season due to low viewership.<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Morrow|first=Michele|user=michelemorrow |number=977965053138812930|date=March 25, 2018|title=“@YouTube cancelled Good Game” #DisappointmentIn4Words|language=en|access-date=May 26, 2018}}</ref>
===Casting=== Alongside the initial series announcement, it was confirmed that the series would star [[Arin Hanson]], [[Dan Avidan]], and [[Michele Morrow]].<ref name="SeriesOrder"/>
==Release== On August 03, 2017, the official trailer for the series was released.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wilde |first1=Tyler |title=Watch the first trailer for the Dan Harmon-produced esports comedy series |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/watch-the-first-trailer-for-the-dan-harmon-produced-esports-comedy-series/ |website=[[PC Gamer]] |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |language=EN-GB |date=August 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=McWhertor |first1=Michael |title=Watch the first trailer for Good Game from Dan Harmon and YouTube Red |url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/8/3/16092002/good-game-trailer-game-grumps-dan-harmon-youtube-red |website=Polygon |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |date=August 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Workman |first1=Robert |title=Rick And Morty Co-Creator Producing New Esports Comedy, Good Game |url=https://comicbook.com/gaming/2017/08/04/rick-and-morty-co-creator-contributes-to-new-esports-comedy-good/ |website=ComicBook.com |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |language=en |date=August 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Gutelle |first1=Sam |title=Game Grumps Offers Preview For 'Good Game' Ahead Of August 30 Premiere On YouTube Red - Tubefilter |url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/08/04/game-grumps-good-game-youtube-red-trailer/ |website=[[Tubefilter]] |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |date=August 4, 2017}}</ref>
