==Reception== In a positive review, ''[[Heavy.com|Heavy]]''{{'}}s Jack Fennimore comended the series saying, "''Good Game'' so far has me impressed. This was clearly a show made by game players, for game players, which is a rarity in most entertainment media. It also made me care about my YouTube Red subscription. And if you have a subscription, I definitely recommend checking the show out. It’s going in a good direction and I can’t wait to see what happens to eSports People."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fennimore |first1=Jack |title=Good Game by Game Grumps Impressions: How Is the&nbsp;Show? |url=https://heavy.com/games/2017/08/good-game-grumps-impressions-youtube-red-esports-jesse-cox/ |website=[[Heavy.com|Heavy]] |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |date=August 30, 2017}}</ref> In another favorable critique, ''[[Wikia|Fandom]]''{{'}}s Drew Dietsch praised the series saying, "The plot itself is a little threadbare, but it clearly gives Arin and Dan a chance to showcase their unique comedic chops. Game Grumps is known for its off-the-cuff ridiculousness, so it’s great that energy has been channeled into something structured. Creators Jesse Cox and Michele Morrow have done an excellent job in having their stars fit the material."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dietsch |first1=Drew |title=‘Good Game’ Gives YouTube Stars Game Grumps Some Structure to Their Silliness |url=http://fandom.wikia.com/articles/good-game-game-grumps-youtube-red |website=[[Wikia|Fandom]] |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |date=August 30, 2017}}</ref> In a more mixed assessment, ''Cultured Vultures''{{'}}s Katrina Bertz described the series as "a poorly-crafted show with a profound message of individual happiness within. I would suggest watching this show with the knowledge that it won’t be good, but its theme will tug at your heartstrings. Just try to overcome your initial confusion and discover something wonderful."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bertz |first1=Katrina |title=Good Game: A Horrible Show and Why You Should Watch It |url=https://culturedvultures.com/good-game-horrible-show-watch/ |website=Cultured Vultures |accessdate=September 28, 2018 |date=November 21, 2017}}</ref>
