{{Infobox school | name = Taras Shevchenko State Art School | native_name = Державна художня середня школа ім. Тараса Шевченка | image = Shevchenko State Art School (1940).jpg | alt = | caption = The school in 1940 | address = 4 Zhambyla Zhabajeva St | motto = | city = Kyiv | country = Ukraine | coordinates = {{coord|50|28|01|N|30|26|00|E|type:edu|display=inline,title}} | established = {{Start date|1937|18|12|df=y}} | opened = | closed = | type = | district = | grades = | superintendent = | principal = | viceprincipal = | enrollment = | faculty = | campus_type = | campus_size = | team_name = | newspaper = | colors = | communities = | feeders = | website = {{URL|dergartschool.kiev.ua}} | footnotes = }} [[File:1940 Kyiv Art School graduation class.jpg|thumb|The first graduation class from the Shevchenko State Art School, 1940.]] '''Taras Shevchenko State Art School''' ({{lang-uk|Державна художня середня школа імені Тараса Шевченка}}) is a [[Selective school|selective high school]] (5th through 12th grade) specializing in [[fine arts]] (painting, sculpture and architecture), in [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]].<ref name="History"/> The school is part of the complex that also includes schools of [[ballet]] and [[music]]. It is located adjoining a historic park overlooking the Southern end of [[Babi Yar]].
The school was established on August 12, 1937, and was originally located at 2 Volodymyrska Street, Kiev (now the [[National Museum of the History of Ukraine]]). The first pupils graduated in 1940. Due to the [[German invasion of the Soviet Union]] in 1941, all the graduates from this class as well as the directors of the school were conscripted into the [[Soviet Army]] and sent to the [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]].<ref name="History"/>
There are many notable artists among its graduates.
==Notable alumni== {{Div col|colwidth=15em}} *[[Kost Lavro]] *[[Yuri Makoveychuk]] *[[Alina Panova]] *[[Arsen Savadov]] *[[Mikhail Turovsky]] *[[Roman Turovsky]] *[[Galyna Zubchenko]] *[[Les Podervyansky]] *[[Christina Katrakis]]
{{Div col end}}
